<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,574,402,465]" box="[151,574,402,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,574,402,429]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" reason="1">
<taxonomicName authority="Lima &amp; Vieira 2017" box="[151,574,402,429]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,574,402,429]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,319,402,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brycon dulcis</emphasis>
<collectingRegion box="[326,393,402,428]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Lima</collectingRegion>
&amp; Vieira 2017
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,574,402,465]" box="[151,521,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,308,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Local names.</emphasis>
Piabanha, biririca.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,510,1005]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,584,510,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Distribution and additional records</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[601,759,511,537]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis box="[601,759,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brycon dulcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from the middle and lower rio Doce basin, in the 
<collectingRegion box="[193,344,547,573]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[399,560,547,573]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[574,704,547,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
<collectingRegion box="[574,635,547,573]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Lima</collectingRegion>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). The species was reported specifically from 
<collectingRegion box="[1213,1436,547,573]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Espírito Santo State</collectingRegion>
only from the Lagoa Juparanã system, with the last record from the state in 1965, from which it was inferred that the species might have been extirpated from the lower portion of the rio Doce basin (
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[1163,1296,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
<collectingRegion box="[1163,1224,619,645]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Lima</collectingRegion>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Somewhat surprisingly, a juvenile specimen was collected in 
<date box="[714,864,655,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2014-01">
January 
<quantity box="[808,864,655,681]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.11556" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" unit="in" value="2014.0">2014</quantity>
</date>
in the Lagoa de Juparanã (UMMZ 250042), which demonstrates that, despite the odds, 
<taxonomicName box="[564,664,691,717]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis box="[564,664,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. dulcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still survives in the lower portion of the rio Doce basin. Recently a single 
<taxonomicName box="[225,323,727,753]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis box="[225,323,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. dulcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimen (MBML 13000, 
<figureCitation box="[627,715,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1549,1573]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1029,1526]" captionTargetId="figure-359@3.[151,1436,1029,1526]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Brycon dulcis, MBML 13000, 250,0 mm SL: Brazil, Espírito Santo, rio Doce basin." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5733626" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5733626/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">figure 2</figureCitation>
) was captured downstream from Cachoeira do Oito hydropower dam, in the Colatina, 
<collectingRegion box="[401,566,763,789]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, confirming that this species still occurs in the lower section of rio Doce in 
<collectingRegion box="[151,317,799,825]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[331,476,799,825]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
<collectingRegion box="[331,390,799,825]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Lima</collectingRegion>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
also commented on a possible previous occurrence of the species in the rio Santa Maria da Vitória, based on some old lots putatively collected from this river basin. João L. Gasparini (pers. comm.) reported that old fishermen from that area mentioned the previous existence of a fish that was very likely a 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1355,1436,871,896]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brycon</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
at the rio Santa Maria da Vitória, known by them as biririca (a name still employed for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Steindachner" authorityYear="1877" box="[1245,1364,907,932]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis box="[1245,1364,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">B. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at the rio Itabapoana (
<bibRefCitation author="Lima, F. C. T." box="[327,456,943,969]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" pagination="1 - 189" refId="ref11148" refString="Lima, F. C. T. (2017) A revision of the cis-andean species of the genus Brycon Muller &amp; Troschel (Characiformes: Characidae). Zootaxa, 4222 (1), 1 - 189. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4222.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">
<collectingRegion box="[327,388,943,969]" country="Peru" name="Lima" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Lima</collectingRegion>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). So, apparently, 
<taxonomicName box="[648,803,943,969]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis box="[648,803,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brycon dulcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
once had a distribution extending southward into the rio Santa Maria da Vitória.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5733626" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5733626" box="[151,1131,1549,1574]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5733626/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" startId="3.[151,250,1549,1573]" targetBox="[151,1436,1029,1526]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1131,1549,1574]" box="[151,1131,1549,1574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,275,1549,1574]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority=", MBML" authorityName="MBML" box="[281,510,1550,1574]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis box="[281,422,1550,1574]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brycon dulcis</emphasis>
, MBML
</taxonomicName>
13000, 250,0 mm SL: Brazil, Espírito Santo, rio Doce basin.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1620,1898]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,546,1620,1646]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Habitat and ecological notes</emphasis>
. The Lagoa de Juparanã on the lower rio Doce is the largest coastal lake in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,219,1656,1682]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sarmento-Soares, L. M. &amp; Martins-Pinheiro, R. F. &amp; Rodrigues, L. N." box="[234,560,1656,1682]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" pagination="9 - 26" refId="ref11809" refString="Sarmento-Soares, L. M., Martins-Pinheiro, R. F. &amp; Rodrigues, L. N. (2017) Peixes do rio Doce segundo as colecoes. Boletim Sociedade Brasileira de Ictiologia, 123, 9 - 26." type="journal article" year="2017">
Sarmento-Soares 
<emphasis box="[435,492,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Today, the Juparanã is inhabited by numerous allochthonous species, typical of lentic environments of other biomes such as the piranha 
<taxonomicName authority="Kner" authorityName="Kner" authorityYear="1858" box="[840,1152,1692,1718]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Serrasalmidae" genus="Pygocentrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nattereri">
<emphasis box="[840,1086,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Pygocentrus nattereri</emphasis>
Kner
</taxonomicName>
and the tucunaré 
<taxonomicName authority="Kullander &amp; Ferreira. The" authorityName="Kullander &amp; Ferreira. The" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Cichla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kelberi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Cichla kelberi</emphasis>
Kullander &amp; Ferreira. The
</taxonomicName>
collapse of Lagoa do Juparanã, mainly caused by eutrophication and habitat destruction, changed its fauna composition (E.H. de Barros, pers. comm.), and most of the native species that previously occurred in the lake are now rare. This is the case of 
<taxonomicName box="[869,1024,1800,1826]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Bryconidae" genus="Brycon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Characiformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="dulcis">
<emphasis box="[869,1024,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Brycon dulcis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an inhabitant of shallow waters and feeding on allochthonous resources, and its populations are possibly vulnerable to predation by the piranhas, and the juveniles, by 
<taxonomicName box="[342,502,1872,1898]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Cichlidae" genus="Cichla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kelberi">
<emphasis box="[342,502,1872,1898]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Cichla kelberi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
